    id: 'a11y-audit',
    category: 'Design',
    title: 'Accessibility Audit',
    desc: 'Comprehensive WCAG compliance review for any interface',
    prompt: 'Act as a senior accessibility engineer and WCAG auditor. Perform a comprehensive accessibility audit of the specified interface.\n\nInterface: [Page/component/app description]\nPlatform: [Web / iOS / Android]\nAudience: [General public / Enterprise / Government / Education]\nKnown Issues: [Any previously reported accessibility concerns]\n\nAudit against these WCAG 2.2 criteria:\n\n1. PERCEIVABLE\n   - All non-text content has text alternatives (1.1.1)\n   - Captions provided for prerecorded audio (1.2.2)\n   - Information and structure separable from presentation (1.3.1)\n   - Content adapts without losing meaning when zoomed 400% (1.4.10)\n   - Color contrast: text 4.5:1, large text 3:1, UI components 3:1 (1.4.11)\n   - Text spacing overrides don\'t break content (1.4.12)\n\n2. OPERABLE\n   - All functionality via keyboard (2.1.1)\n   - No keyboard traps (2.1.2)\n   - Focus order preserves logical reading sequence (2.4.3)\n   - Link purpose clear from text alone (2.4.4)\n   - Focus indicator at least 2px thick with 3:1 contrast (2.4.13)\n   - Motion animation triggered by interaction can be disabled (2.3.3)\n   - Pointer gestures have single-point alternatives (2.5.1)\n   - Target size at least 24x24px (2.5.8)\n\n3. UNDERSTANDABLE\n   - Language set programmatically (3.1.1)\n   - Purpose of input fields collectible/autofillable (3.3.7)\n   - Error identification: clearly describe what went wrong (3.3.1)\n   - Error suggestions: provide specific fix recommendations (3.3.3)\n   - Error prevention for legal/financial transactions (3.3.4)\n\n4. ROBUST\n   - Semantic HTML elements used correctly (4.1.1)\n   - ARIA attributes used according to spec (4.1.2)\n   - Status messages announced by screen readers (4.1.3)\n\nFor each issue, provide:\n- WCAG criterion violated\n- Severity (Critical / Major / Minor)\n- Where the issue occurs (specific element or pattern)\n- How to reproduce (including assistive technology used)\n- Specific fix with code example\n- Before/after screen reader output\n\nInclude an executive summary with total issues by severity and estimated remediation effort.',
