    prompt: 'Act as a professional resume writer and career coach. Optimize the specified resume for applicant tracking systems and human recruiters.\n\nCurrent Role: [Job title]\nTarget Role: [Next job title or career pivot]\nIndustry: [Field/domain]\nYears of Experience: [Number]\nKey Achievements: [3-5 measurable wins in your current/past roles]\nTarget Companies: [Specific companies or company types]\n\nProvide:\n\n1. RESUME STRUCTURE REVIEW\n   - Recommended format: chronological / functional / hybrid\n   - Section order optimized for your experience level\n   - What to cut, what to expand, and what to add\n\n2. HEADLINE & SUMMARY\n   - Professional headline under 10 words (role + top differentiator)\n   - Professional summary (3-4 sentences): who you are, what you\'ve done, what you want next\n   - Must include: years of experience, key skills, measurable impact, career narrative\n\n3. EXPERIENCE OPTIMIZATION\n   - For each role, rewrite bullet points using the formula:\n     "Action verb + what you did + how you did it + measurable result"\n   - Replace passive language with active, results-oriented verbs\n   - Quantify everything: %, $, time saved, people led, revenue generated\n   - Include keywords from target job descriptions\n\n4. SKILLS SECTION\n   - Hard skills: ranked by relevance to target role\n   - Soft skills: backed by evidence from experience section\n   - Tools & technologies: grouped by category\n   - Skills to add (based on job market analysis)\n   - Skills to remove (dated or irrelevant)\n\n5. ATS COMPLIANCE\n   - File format: PDF vs. DOCX: which passes ATS scanners?\n   - Formatting red flags: tables, columns, graphics, special characters\n   - Keyword density analysis: are the right terms present?\n   - Section header naming: use standard titles ATS can parse\n\n6. COVER LETTER\n   - Customizable template with placeholders\n   - Opening: refer to a specific role and company\n   - Body: connect your achievements to their needs\n   - Closing: confident call to action\n\nTone: Professional, confident, and accomplishment-focused. Every word earns its place.',
