    title: 'Email Sequence Strategist',
    desc: 'Design automated email sequences that nurture and convert',
    prompt: 'Act as an email marketing automation strategist. Design a complete email sequence for the specified campaign.\n\nCampaign Type: [Welcome series / Lead nurture / Abandoned cart / Re-engagement / Post-purchase / Sales launch]\nTarget Audience: [Who is receiving these emails?]\nOffer: [What are you ultimately selling or promoting?]\nBrand Voice: [Friendly / Professional / Playful / Authoritative / Minimal]\nEmail Platform: [Mailchimp / Klaviyo / ConvertKit / HubSpot / ActiveCampaign]\n\nDesign the full sequence:\n\nEMAIL 1: TRIGGER (send immediately)\n- Subject line: [Curiosity + personalization]\n- Goal: Deliver on the promise that got them here\n- Content: Immediate value (resource, discount, or key insight)\n- CTA: Single, low-friction action\n\nEMAIL 2: FOLLOW-UP (24 hours later)\n- Subject line: [Social proof or story hook]\n- Goal: Build trust and credibility\n- Content: Case study, testimonial, or origin story\n- CTA: Engage with content (read, watch, explore)\n\nEMAIL 3: VALUE (3 days later)\n- Subject line: [How-to or educational angle]\n- Goal: Demonstrate expertise and provide utility\n- Content: Deep dive into a specific problem/solution\n- CTA: Apply what they learned (with your product as the enabler)\n\nEMAIL 4: OBJECTIONS (5 days later)\n- Subject line: [Address a common hesitation]\n- Goal: Overcome barriers to conversion\n- Content: FAQ, comparison, risk reversal, guarantee\n- CTA: Case study or testimonial that addresses their specific doubt\n\nEMAIL 5: OFFER (7 days later)\n- Subject line: [Urgency + benefit]\n- Goal: Drive conversion\n- Content: Clear offer with deadline or scarcity element\n- CTA: Strong, unambiguous purchase/demo/signup button\n\nEMAIL 6: LAST CHANCE (10 days later)\n- Subject line: [FOMO + recap of value]\n- Goal: Final conversion attempt\n- Content: Summary of benefits + final deadline\n- CTA: Last opportunity with urgency\n\nFor each email:\n- Preheader text that complements subject line\n- Body: 1-3 short paragraphs, scannable\n- Button text and color psychology rationale\n- Personalization variables to use\n- Expected open rate benchmark\n\nConstraints:\n- Spacing between emails based on user behavior triggers, not just time\n- Every email has ONE goal: no competing CTAs\n- Respect GDPR/CAN-SPAM: clear unsubscribe in every email\n- Mobile-first: buttons >44px, single column, short subject lines\n- Include a "breakup" sequence for non-responders after email 6\n- Track: open rate, click rate, conversion rate, unsubscribe rate',
