    desc: 'Set ambitious, measurable goals with a clear action plan',
    prompt: 'Act as an OKR coach and strategic planning facilitator. Help me define and plan ambitious goals using the OKR framework.\n\nTeam/Company: [Department or organization name]\nMission: [Your team\'s purpose in one sentence]\nTime Period: [Quarter / Half-year / Year]\nCurrent Challenges: [Top 3 obstacles to progress]\nResources Available: [Budget, headcount, tools, partnerships]\n\nCreate OKRs:\n\n1. OBJECTIVE 1: [Ambitious, qualitative goal]\n   - Why this matters: [Connection to company mission]\n   - Key Results (3-5 measurable outcomes):\n     - KR1: [Metric] from [current] to [target] by [date]\n     - KR2: [Metric] from [current] to [target] by [date]\n     - KR3: [Metric] from [current] to [target] by [date]\n   - Confidence level: [50% / 60% / 70%]: OKRs should stretch, not guarantee\n   - Initiatives (actions to achieve this objective):\n     - [Initiative 1 with owner and deadline]\n     - [Initiative 2 with owner and deadline]\n     - [Initiative 3 with owner and deadline]\n\n2. OBJECTIVE 2: [Second ambitious goal]\n   - [Same structure as Objective 1]\n\n3. OBJECTIVE 3: [Third goal: consider a health/metrics goal]\n   - [Same structure]\n\nFor each OKR:\n- Leading vs. lagging indicators: identify which KRs predict success (leading) vs. measure it (lagging)\n- Dependency mapping: what needs to be true for this OKR to succeed?\n- Weekly check-in format: progress update, blockers, next steps\n- Stretch target: if everything goes perfectly, what\'s possible?\n\nConstraints:\n- Objectives are inspirational and qualitative: not a task list\n- Key Results are quantitative and measurable: every KR must have a number\n- 3-5 KRs per objective (any more and focus dilutes)\n- Set the bar high: 60-70% achievement is success (if you always hit 100%, you\'re not stretching)\n- Align with company-level OKRs: how does team success roll up?\n- Include both output metrics (what we deliver) and outcome metrics (what changes as a result)\n\nFinal output: One-page OKR document ready for team review.',
