    id: 'swot-analysis',
    category: 'Business',
    title: 'SWOT & Strategy Planner',
    desc: 'Analyze strengths, weaknesses, opportunities, and threats',
    prompt: 'Act as a business strategy consultant. Conduct a comprehensive SWOT analysis and strategic recommendation for the specified business or project.\n\nBusiness/Project: [Name and description]\nIndustry: [Sector and market context]\nSize/Stage: [Startup / Growth / Mature / Non-profit]\nCompetitors: [Top 3-5 competitors]\nGoals: [Short-term and long-term objectives]\nData Available: [Revenue, users, market share, NPS, churn: whatever is available]\n\nSWOT Analysis:\n\n1. STRENGTHS (Internal, Positive)\n   - What do you do better than anyone else?\n   - What unique resources or capabilities do you have?\n   - What do customers/competitors see as your greatest advantage?\n   - For each strength: how sustainable is it? (6 months, 2 years, 5 years)\n\n2. WEAKNESSES (Internal, Negative)\n   - Where are you underperforming vs. competitors?\n   - What resources or capabilities are you missing?\n   - What do customers complain about most?\n   - For each weakness: what\'s the root cause? (resource gap, skill gap, process issue)\n\n3. OPPORTUNITIES (External, Positive)\n   - What market trends can you capitalize on?\n   - What unmet customer needs exist?\n   - What technology changes create new possibilities?\n   - What regulatory or demographic shifts work in your favor?\n   - For each opportunity: what\'s the window to act?\n\n4. THREATS (External, Negative)\n   - What are competitors doing that could hurt you?\n   - What market trends work against you?\n   - What regulatory changes could impact operations?\n   - What technology changes could disrupt your model?\n   - For each threat: probability (Low/Medium/High) and impact (Low/Medium/High)\n\nCross-Analysis & Strategy:\n\n5. SO STRATEGIES (Use strengths to capture opportunities)\n   - [Specific action leveraging a strength toward an opportunity]\n\n6. WO STRATEGIES (Improve weaknesses to pursue opportunities)\n   - [Specific action to address a weakness and seize an opportunity]\n\n7. ST STRATEGIES (Use strengths to defend against threats)\n   - [Specific action using a strength to mitigate a threat]\n\n8. WT STRATEGIES (Minimize weaknesses and avoid threats)\n   - [Defensive action to reduce weakness exposure to threats]\n\n9. PRIORITIZED RECOMMENDATIONS\n   - Top 3 actions ranked by impact/effort\n   - Timeline: immediate (30 days), short-term (90 days), medium-term (6 months)\n   - Resources required and expected ROI for each\n   - Key metrics to track progress\n\nTone: Objective, data-driven, and strategic. Support every claim with evidence where possible. Clearly separate facts from opinions.',
